The '''Javan tesia''' ('''''Tesia superciliaris''''') is a species of [[Old World warbler]] in the family [[Cettiidae]]. It is [[endemism|endemic]] to [[Java]] in [[Indonesia]]. The Javan tesia is a small tesia with long legs and almost no tail. It feeds on [[insects]] in the undergrowth of [[Tropical and subtropical moist broadleaf forests|broadleaf forest]].

